#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/undo-redo.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Most changes made within the lighttable are recorded and can be reverted to a previous state. This includes modifications to color labels, ratings, geo-localization, tags, metadata, orientation, copy/paste of history, image duplication, or application of a style. Note that the facility to undo/redo actions is unlimited in the number of steps while in the lighttable view, but it is reset each time you switch to a different view.\n"
msgstr "La plupart des modifications de la table lumineuse sont enregistrées et peuvent être annulées. Cela inclut les modifications apportées aux labels de couleur, aux évaluations, à la géolocalisation, aux mots-clés, aux métadonnées, à l'orientation, au copier/coller de l'historique, au clonage de l'image ou à l'application d'un style. Notez que cette fonction annuler/refaire accepte un nombre illimité d'enregistrements d'états tant qu'on reste dans la table lumineuse, mais elle est réinitialisée à chaque fois que vous passez à une autre vue.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lua/_index.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Scripting with Lua"
msgstr "Automatisation avec Lua"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/_index.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "darktable comes with a versatile scripting interface language for functionality enhancement.\n"
msgstr "darktable est livré avec un langage d'interface de script polyvalent pour améliorer ses fonctionnalités.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lua/a-simple-example.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "a simple lua example"
msgstr "Un exemple lua simple"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/a-simple-example.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Let's start with a simple example that will print some code on the console. Create a file called `luarc` in darktable's configuration directory (usually `$HOME/.config/darktable/`) and add the following line to it:\n"
msgstr "Commençons par un exemple simple qui affiche du code sur la console. Créez un fichier appelé `luarc` dans le répertoire de configuration de darktable (généralement `$HOME/.config/darktable/`) et ajoutez-y la ligne suivante :\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/lua/a-simple-example.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "print(\"Hello World !\")\n"
msgstr "print(\"Hello World !\")\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/a-simple-example.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Start darktable and you will see the sentence \"`Hello World !`\" printed on the console. Nothing fancy but it's a start.\n"
msgstr "Lancez darktable et vous verrez la phrase \"`Hello World !`\" s'afficher sur la console. Rien d'extraordinaire, mais c'est un début.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/a-simple-example.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "At this point, there is nothing darktable-specific in the script. We simply use Lua's standard print function to print a string. That's nice and all, but we can do better than that. To access the darktable API you first need to `require` it and save the returned object in a variable. Once this is done you can access the darktable API as subfields of the returned object. All of this is documented in darktable's [Lua API](./api.md) reference manual.\n"
msgstr "À ce stade, il n'y a rien de spécifique à darktable dans le script. Nous utilisons simplement la fonction d'affichage standard de Lua, permettant d'afficher une chaîne de caractère. C'est bien beau, mais nous pouvons faire mieux. Ainsi pour accéder à l'API darktable, vous devez d'abord la `require` et enregistrer le retour dans une variable. Depuis cette variable, vous pouvez accéder à toute l'API darktable en appelant des sous-champs. Tout est documenté dans le manuel de l'[API Lua](./api.md)\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/lua/a-simple-example.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"local darktable = require \"darktable\"\n"
"darktable.print_error(\"Hello World !\")\n"
msgstr ""
"local darktable = require \"darktable\"\n"
"darktable.print_error(\"Hello World !\")\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/a-simple-example.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Run the script and ... nothing happens. The function `darktable.print_error` is just like `print` but will only print the message if you have enabled lua traces by running darktable with \"`darktable -d lua`\" on the command line. This is the recommended way to do traces in a darktable lua script.\n"
msgstr "Exécutez le script et... rien de ne s'affiche ! La fonction `darktable.print_error` est comme le `print` classique mais affiche le message uniquement si vous avez activé les traces Lua en lançant darktable avec la commande `darktable -d lua`. C'est la méthode recommandée pour afficher des traces dans un script Lua de darktable.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lua/api.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "lua API"
msgstr "API Lua"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/api.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "darktable's Lua API is documented in its own manual with a detailed description of all data structures and functions. You can download the API manual from [here](https://www.darktable.org/resources/).\n"
msgstr "L'API Lua de darktable est documentée avec son propre manuel comprenant une description détaillée de toutes les structures de données et fonctions. Vous pouvez télécharger le manuel de l'API à partir de (https://www.darktable.org/resources/).\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lua/basic-principles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "basic principles: luarc files"
msgstr "Principes de base : fichiers luarc"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/basic-principles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "At startup, darktable will automatically run the Lua scripts `$DARKTABLE/share/darktable/luarc` and `$HOME/.config/darktable/luarc` (where `$DARKTABLE` represents the darktable installation directory and `$HOME` represents your home directory).\n"
msgstr "Au démarrage, darktable lancera automatiquement le scripts Lua `$DARKTABLE/share/darktable/luarc`et `$HOME/.config/darktable/luarc` (où `$DARKTABLE`représente le dossier d'installation de darktable et `$HOME` votre dossier utilisateur).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/basic-principles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is the only time darktable will run Lua scripts by itself. These scripts can register callbacks to perform actions on various darktable events. This callback mechanism is the primary method of triggering lua actions.\n"
msgstr "C'est la seule fois que darktable lancera des scripts Lua de lui même. Ces scripts peuvent enregistrer des rappels pour réaliser des actions sur divers évènements de darktable. Ce mécanisme de rappel est la principale méthode de déclenchement d'actions Lua.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lua/building-ui-elements.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "building user interface elements"
msgstr "Constructions d'éléments de l'interface utilisateur"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/building-ui-elements.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our previous example was a bit limited. In particular the use of a preference for the export path wasn't very nice. We can do better than that by adding elements to the user interface in the export dialog.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/building-ui-elements.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "UI elements are created via the `darktable_new_widget` function. This function takes a type of widget as a parameter and returns a new object corresponding to that widget. You can then set various fields in that widget to set its parameters. You will then use that object as a parameter to various functions that will add it to the darktable UI. The following simple example adds a lib in the lighttable view with a simple label:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/lua/building-ui-elements.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"local my_label = darktable.new_widget(\"label\")\n"
"my_label.label = \"Hello, world !\"\n"
"\n"
"dt.register_lib(\"test\",\"test\",false,{\n"
"    [dt.gui.views.lighttable] = {\"DT_UI_CONTAINER_PANEL_LEFT_CENTER\",20},\n"
"    },my_label)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/building-ui-elements.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is a nice syntactic trick to make UI elements code easier to read and write. You can call these objects as functions with a table of key values as an argument. This allows the following example to work. It creates a container widget with two sub-widgets: a label and a text entry field.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/lua/building-ui-elements.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   local my_widget = darktable.new_widget(\"box\"){\n"
"      orientation = \"horizontal\",\n"
"      darktable.new_widget(\"label\"){ label = \"here => \" },\n"
"      darktable.new_widget(\"entry\"){ tooltip = \"please enter text here\" }\n"
"   }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/building-ui-elements.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now that we know that, let's improve our script a bit.\n"
msgstr "Maintenant que nous le savons, allons améliorer un peu notre script.\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/lua/building-ui-elements.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"darktable = require \"darktable\"\n"
"\n"
"local scp_path = darktable.new_widget(\"entry\"){\n"
"  tooltip =\"Complete path to copy to. Can include user and hostname\",\n"
"  text = \"\",\n"
"  reset_callback = function(self) self.text = \"\" end\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"darktable.register_storage(\"scp_export\",\"Export via scp\",\n"
"  function( storage, image, format, filename,\n"
"     number, total, high_quality, extra_data)\n"
"    if not darktable.control.execute(scp \"..filename..\" \"..\n"
"      scp_path.text\n"
"    ) then\n"
"      darktable.print_error(\"scp failed for \"..tostring(image))\n"
"    end\n"
"    end,\n"
"    nil, --finalize\n"
"    nil, --supported\n"
"    nil, --initialize\n"
"    darktable.new_widget(\"box\") {\n"
"    orientation =\"horizontal\",\n"
"    darktable.new_widget(\"label\"){label = \"target SCP PATH \"},\n"
"    scp_path,\n"
"})\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lua/calling-from-dbus.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "calling lua from dbus"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/calling-from-dbus.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is possible to send a lua command to darktable via its DBus interface. The method `org.darktable.service.Remote.Lua` takes a single string parameter which is interpreted as a lua command. The command will be executed in the current lua context and should return either nil or a string. The result will be passed back as the result of the DBus method.\n"
msgstr "Il est possible d'envoyer une commande Lua à darktable via son interface DBus. La méthode `org.darktable.service.Remote.Lua` prend une seule chaîne de paramètre qui est interprétée comme une commande Lua. La commande sera exécutée dans le contexte Lua en cours et devrait retourner soit nul soit une chaîne. Le résultat sera accrédité en tant que résultat de la méthode DBus.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/calling-from-dbus.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "If the Lua call results in an error, the DBus method call will return an error `org.darktable.Error.LuaError` with the lua error message as the message attached to the DBus error. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lua/darktable-from-lua.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "using darktable from a lua script"
msgstr "utiliser darktable depuis un script lua"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/darktable-from-lua.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "_Warning: This feature is very experimental. It is known that several elements don't yet work in library mode. Careful testing is highly recommended._\n"
msgstr "_Attention  : Cette fonctionnalité est très expérimentale. Il est reconnu que plusieurs éléments de fonctionnent pas encore en mode bibliothèque. Des tests prudents sont hautement recommandés.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/darktable-from-lua.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The lua interface allows you to use darktable from any lua script. This will load darktable as a library and provide you with most of the lua API (darktable is configured headless, so the functions relating to the user interface are not available).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/darktable-from-lua.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "As an example, the following program will print the list of all images in your library:\n"
msgstr "Par exemple, le programme suivant écrira la liste de toutes les images dans votre bibliothèque.\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/lua/darktable-from-lua.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#!/usr/bin/env lua\n"
"package = require \"package\"\n"
"package.cpath=package.cpath..\";./lib/darktable/lib?.so\"\n"
"\n"
"dt = require(\"darktable\")(\n"
"\"--library\", \"./library.db\",\n"
"\"--datadir\", \"./share/darktable\",\n"
"\"--moduledir\", \"./lib/darktable\",\n"
"\"--configdir\", \"./configdir\",\n"
"\"--cachedir\",\"cachedir\",\n"
"\"--g-fatal-warnings\")\n"
"\n"
"require(\"darktable.debug\")\n"
"\n"
"for k,v in ipairs(dt.database) do\n"
"   print(tostring(v))\n"
"end\n"
msgstr ""
"#!/usr/bin/env lua\n"
"package = require \"package\"\n"
"package.cpath=package.cpath..\";./lib/darktable/lib?.so\"\n"
"\n"
"dt = require(\"darktable\")(\n"
"\"--library\", \"./library.db\",\n"
"\"--datadir\", \"./share/darktable\",\n"
"\"--moduledir\", \"./lib/darktable\",\n"
"\"--configdir\", \"./configdir\",\n"
"\"--cachedir\",\"cachedir\",\n"
"\"--g-fatal-warnings\")\n"
"\n"
"require(\"darktable.debug\")\n"
"\n"
"for k,v in ipairs(dt.database) do\n"
"   print(tostring(v))\n"
"end\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/darktable-from-lua.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Note the third line that points to the location of the `libdarktable.so` file.\n"
msgstr "Notez la troisième ligne qui pointe vers l'emplacement du fichier `libdarktable.so`.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/darktable-from-lua.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Also note that the call to require returns a function that can be called only once and allows you to set darktable's command line parameter. The `:memory:` parameter to `--library` is useful here if you don't want to work on your personal library.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "exporting images with lua"
msgstr "export d'image avec lua"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "So far we have learned to use lua to adapt darktable to our particular workflow. Let's look now at how to use lua to easily export images to an online service. If you are able to upload an image to a service via the command line then you can use lua to integrate this into darktable's user interface.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "In this next example we will use lua to export via `scp`. A new storage type will appear in darktable's UI that will export images to a remote target via the copy mechanism in `ssh`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"darktable = require \"darktable\"\n"
"\n"
"darktable.preferences.register(\"scp_export\",\"export_path\",\n"
"  \"string\",\"target SCP path\",\n"
"  \"Complete path to copy to. Can include user and hostname\",\"\")\n"
"\n"
"darktable.register_storage(\"scp_export\",\"Export via scp\",\n"
"  function( storage, image, format, filename,\n"
"     number, total, high_quality, extra_data)\n"
"    if not darktable.control.execute(\"scp \"..filename..\" \"..\n"
"      darktable.preferences.read(\"scp_export\",\n"
"         \"export_path\",\"string\")) then\n"
"      darktable.print_error(\"scp failed for \"..tostring(image))\n"
"    end\n"
"end)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`darktable.preferences.register` will add a new preference to darktable's preferences menu, `scp_export` and `export_path` allow us to uniquely identify our preference. These fields are reused when we read the value of the preference. The `string` field tells the lua engine that the preference is a string. It could also be an integer, a filename or any of the types detailed in the API manual relating to `types_lua_pref_type` . We then have the label for the preference in the preference menu, the tooltip when hovering over the value and a default value.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`darktable.register_storage` is the call that actually registers a new storage type. The first argument is a name for the storage type, the second is the label that will be displayed in the UI and last is a function to call on each image. This function has a lot of parameters, but `filename` is the only one we use in this example. It contains the name of a temporary file where the image was exported by darktable's engine.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "This code will work but it has a couple of limitations. This is just a simple example after all:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "We use preferences to configure the target path. It would be nicer to add an element to the export UI in darktable. We will detail how to do that in the next section.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "We do not check the returned value of `scp`. That command might fail, in particular if the user has not correctly set the preference.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/lua/exporting-images.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "This script can't read input from the user. The remote `scp` must use password-less copy -- `scp` can't be provided with a password easily, so we will leave it that way.\n"
