#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "A list of all available styles is displayed in the module. A search field above the list allows you to locate a style by name or description. This module also allows styles to be edited and deleted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Double-click on a style name to apply that style to all selected images.  A style may also be applied to all selected images by pressing a shortcut key assigned to it (see [preferences > shortcuts](../../../preferences-settings/shortcuts.md)) while in the lighttable or darkroom view.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Remove all styles by clicking on the module's reset button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please note that styles also include the active state of each module. You can use this to create your own default settings, which you can then activate on-demand. Simply set your desired defaults for each module, disable the module, and save the style.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"create duplicate\n"
": When applying a style to images, tick this box to create a duplicate of each image before applying the chosen style to that duplicate. Disable this option to apply the chosen style directly to the selected images. Beware that in this case any existing history stack is overwritten (depending on the mode -- see below) and cannot be recovered.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mode\n"
": As with the [history stack](./history-stack.md) module, this combobox allows you to either \"append\" the style to the current history stack or to \"overwrite\" the history stack of the target image.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"create\n"
": Create new style(s) using the history stack of the selected image(s). For each selected image a style creation window is shown. You must supply a unique name for each new style and you can also add an optional description. You will be given the option to de-select any history stack items that you don't want to be part of the created style.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": The panel supports a hierarchical view, meaning that you can create categories using the pipe symbol “|” as a separator. For example “print|tone curve +0.5 EV” will create a \"print\" category with a style of \"tone curve +0.5 EV\" below it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"edit\n"
": Select \"edit\" to bring up a dialog which allows you to include or exclude specific items from the stack of an existing style. Check the “duplicate” option if you want to create a new style, instead of overwriting the existing one, in which case you will need to provide a unique name for the new style.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"remove\n"
": Delete the selected style, without any further prompt.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"import\n"
": Import a previously saved style. Styles are stored as XML files with the extension `.dtstyle`. If a style with the same name already exists, you will be asked if you wish to overwrite.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"export\n"
": Save the selected style to disk as a `.dtstyle` file. This allows styles to be published and shared with other users.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/timeline.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "timeline"
msgstr "chronologie"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/timeline.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "View your images by the date/time they were taken.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/timeline.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "![timeline](./timeline/timeline.png)\n"
msgstr "![chronologie](./timeline/timeline.png)\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/timeline.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the lighttable filemanager view, you can show/hide the timeline module in the bottom panel with the shortcut Ctrl+F. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/timeline.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Within the timeline, you can show the next and previous dates by scrolling your mouse; Ctrl+scroll to zoom in/out.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/timeline.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can also use the timeline to select images by date range by clicking and dragging your mouse.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manipulate the history stack of one or more selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"selective copy...\n"
": Copy parts of the history stack from the selected image. A dialog appears from which you may choose the items to copy from the history stack. If more than one image is selected, the history stack is taken from the image that was selected first. Double-click on a history item to copy that item only and immediately close the dialog.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"copy\n"
": Copy the complete history stack from the selected image. If more than one image is selected, the history stack is taken from the image that was selected first.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": Information relating to internal display encoding and mask management is considered unsafe to automatically copy to other images and will therefore not be copied when using this button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": The following modules are excluded from the _copy_ operation:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
": - [_orientation_](../../processing-modules/orientation.md)\n"
": - [_lens correction_](../../processing-modules/lens-correction.md)\n"
": - [_raw black/white point_](../../processing-modules/raw-black-white-point.md)\n"
": - [_rotate pixels_](../../processing-modules/rotate-pixels.md)\n"
": - [_scale pixels_](../../processing-modules/scale-pixels.md)\n"
": - [_white balance_](../../processing-modules/white-balance.md)\n"
": - deprecated modules\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": You can override all of these exclusions by using \"selective paste...\" and choosing which modules to paste to the target image(s).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"compress history\n"
": Compress the history stack of the selected image. If any module appears multiple times in the history stack, these occurrences will be _compressed_ into a single step in the history. _Beware: this action can not be undone!_\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"discard history\n"
": Physically delete the history stack of the selected images. _Beware: this action can not be undone!_\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"selective paste...\n"
": Paste parts of a copied history stack onto all selected images. A dialog appears from which you may choose the items to paste from the source history stack.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"paste\n"
": Paste all items of a copied history stack onto all selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mode\n"
": This setting defines how the paste actions behave when applied to an image that already has a history stack. In simple terms the “overwrite” mode deletes the previous history stack before pasting, whereas “append”  concatenates the two history stacks together.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": A copied history stack can have multiple entries of the same module (with the same name or different names) and pasting behaves differently for these entries in append and overwrite modes. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": In _append_ mode, for each module in the copied history stack, if there is a module in the destination image with the same name it will be replaced. If there is no such module, a new instance will be created. In both cases the pasted instance is placed on top of the history stack. If a particular module appears multiple times in either history stack only the last occurrence of that module will be processed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": In _overwrite_ mode the behavior is the same except that the history of the destination image is deleted before the paste operation commences. The “copy all”/“paste all” actions in this mode will precisely duplicate the copied history stack to the destination images (including any duplicate occurrences).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Notes\n"
": - Automatic module presets are only added to an image when it is first opened in the darkroom or its history stack is discarded. If you use _overwrite_ mode to paste history stack entries to images that haven't previously been opened in the darkroom then the next time that image is opened in the darkroom, automatic presets will be applied to the image. It may therefore seem as if the “overwrite” mode did not accurately duplicate the existing history stack, but in this case, those automatic modules were added subsequently.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": - The _append_ mode allows you to later reconstruct your pre-existing history stack (because previous history items are retained in the stack of the destination image). However, in “overwrite” mode all previous edits are irrevocably lost.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": - The _mode_ setting is retained when you quit darktable -- if you change it for a one-off copy and paste, make sure to change it back again.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"load sidecar file\n"
": Open a dialog box which allows you to import the history stack from a selected XMP file. This copied history stack can then be pasted onto one or more images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": Images that were exported by darktable typically contain the full history stack if the file format supports embedded metadata (see the [export](../shared/export.md) module for details of this feature and its limitations). You can load an exported image as a sidecar file in the same way as you can with an XMP file. This feature allows you to recover all parameter settings if you have accidentally lost or overwritten the XMP file. All you need is the source image, typically a raw, and the exported file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"write sidecar files\n"
": Write XMP sidecar files for all selected images. The filename is generated by appending “.xmp” to the name of the underlying input file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": By default darktable generates and updates sidecar files automatically whenever you work on an image and change the history stack. You can disable automatic sidecar file generation in [preferences > storage](../../../preferences-settings/storage.md). This can be useful when you are running multiple versions of darktable (so that edits in each version do not conflict with one another) however, in general, disabling this feature is not recommended.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "selected images"
msgstr "images sélectionnées"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Perform actions on images that have been selected in the lighttable view.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The module controls are spread over two tabs for manipulating the image files and the related metadata.\n"
msgstr "Les contrôles du module sont répartis en deux onglets pour manipuler, l'un les fichiers images, et l'autre les métadonnées associées.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "images tab"
msgstr "onglet images"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"remove\n"
": Remove the selected images from the darktable library without deleting them. Removed images can no longer be viewed or edited within darktable but the image files remain on the filesystem along with any XMP sidecar files. As darktable keeps the XMP files up-to-date with your latest development history, you can fully restore your work later by re-importing the images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"delete / delete (trash)\n"
": Remove the selected images from the darktable library and remove any associated XMP sidecar files from the filesystem. If no duplicates of a removed image remain in the darktable library, the image file itself is also deleted. You can control whether this action irrevocably deletes the files or attempts to put them into your system's trash bin with a configuration item in [preferences > security](../../../preferences-settings/security.md). A second configuration item in the same tab allows you to control whether or not to be prompted before deleting images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"move\n"
": Physically move selected images (the image files plus all associated XMP sidecars) to another folder on the filesystem. If an image with the given filename already exists in the target folder the source image will not be moved.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"copy\n"
": Physically copy selected images (the image file plus all associated XMP sidecars) to another folder on the filesystem. If an image with the given filename already exists in the target folder it will not be overwritten – instead a new duplicate will be generated with the same history stack as the source image.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"create hdr\n"
": Create a high dynamic range image from the selected images, and add the result to the library as a new image in DNG format. Images need to be properly aligned, which implies that they have been taken on a sturdy tripod. You can also generate HDRs with programs like Luminance HDR, and later import them into darktable for further processing. Note that darktable can only create HDR images from raw files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"duplicate\n"
": Create duplicates of the selected images within darktable. Duplicate images share the same image file, but each duplicate has its own XMP sidecar file and a separate entry in darktable's library database. This allows you to test different edits on the same image.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rotation\n"
": Perform a clockwise or counter-clockwise rotation on the selected images. A third button can be used to reset the image rotation to the value stored in the image's Exif data. This feature is directly linked to the [_orientation_](../../../module-reference/processing-modules/orientation.md) processing module -- adjustments made here are automatically converted into a history stack item for that module.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"copy locally\n"
": Create local copies of the selected images on the local drive. These copies will then be used when the original images are not accessible (see [local copies](../../../overview/sidecar-files/local-copies.md)).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"resync local copy\n"
": Synchronize the XMP sidecar of the local copy of each selected image with the copy in external storage, and remove the local copies. Note that if a local copy has been modified and the external storage is not accessible the local copy will not be deleted (see [local copies](../../../overview/sidecar-files/local-copies.md)).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"group\n"
": Create a new group from the selected images (see [image grouping](../../../lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md)).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ungroup\n"
": Remove the selected images from their group (see [image grouping](../../../lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md)).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "metadata tab"
msgstr "onglet métadonnées"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"metadata type checkboxes\n"
": Choose the types of metadata (ratings, tags, metadata, colors, geo tags) that you want to operate on. \n"
msgstr ""
"cases à cocher des types de métadonnées\n"
": Choisissez les types de métadonnées (étoiles, balises, métadonnées, couleurs, géolocalisation) sur lesquels vous souhaitez opérer \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"copy\n"
": Copy the chosen types of metadata from the selected image onto the clipboard. If you have more than one image selected, or no images selected, then this button is unavailable.\n"
msgstr ""
"copier\n"
": Copie les types de métadonnées choisis de l'image sélectionnée dans le presse-papiers. Si plusieurs images sont sélectionnées ou si aucune image n'est sélectionnée, ce bouton n'est pas disponible.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"paste\n"
": Paste any metadata in the clipboard onto the selected images.\n"
msgstr ""
"coller\n"
": colle toutes les métadonnées du presse-papiers sur les images sélectionnées.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"clear\n"
": Clear the chosen types of metadata from the selected images.\n"
msgstr ""
"effacer\n"
": Supprime les types de métadonnées choisis de images sélectionnées.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mode\n"
": When pasting metadata onto images, this option controls whether the metadata on the clipboard should be merged with the existing metadata (_merge_), or should replace it entirely (_overwrite_).\n"
msgstr ""
"mode\n"
": lors du collage de métadonnées sur des images, cette option contrôle si les métadonnées du presse-papiers doivent être fusionnées avec les métadonnées existantes (_fusionner_), ou doivent les remplacer entièrement (_écraser_).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"refresh exif\n"
": Refresh the Exif data from the source file. Warning: this may overwrite some tags and metadata that you have altered in darktable (such as star ratings).\n"
msgstr ""
"rafraîchir exif\n"
": Actualisez les données Exif du fichier source. Attention : cela peut écraser certaines balises et métadonnées que vous avez modifiées dans darktable (comme les étoiles).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"monochrome\n"
": Flag the image as monochrome, meaning that it will receive any monochrome-specific workflow treatment that is offered by the processing modules. Refer to the [developing monochrome images](../../../guides-tutorials/monochrome.md) section for more details.\n"
msgstr ""
"monochrome\n"
": Marque l'image comme monochrome, ce qui signifie qu'elle recevra tout traitement spécifique au flux de travail monochrome. Reportez-vous à la section [développement d'images monochromes](../../../guides-tutorials/monochrome.md) pour plus de détails.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"color\n"
": Remove the monochrome flag from the image so that it will receive the default workflow treatment that is normally used when developing color photos.\n"
msgstr ""
"Couleur\n"
": Supprime le drapeau monochrome de l'image afin qu'il reçoive le traitement de flux de travail par défaut normalement utilisé lors du développement de photos couleur.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#: content/preferences-settings/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "import"
msgstr "importer"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add images to the darktable library, optionally copying them from another location on the filesystem or from a connected camera.\n"
msgstr "Ajoute des images à la bibliothèque darktable, en les copiant éventuellement à partir d'un autre emplacement du système de fichiers ou à partir d'un boîtier connecté.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "See [supported file formats](../../../overview/supported-file-formats.md) for more information.\n"
msgstr "Voir [formats de fichiers pris en charge](../../../overview/supported-file-formats.md) pour plus d'informations.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following buttons are shown in the module's UI by default:\n"
msgstr "Les boutons suivants sont affichés par défaut dans l'interface :\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[add to library](#add-to-library) \n"
": Add existing images to the darktable library without copying or moving files. If you only add a single image to the library it will be automatically loaded in the darkroom.\n"
msgstr ""
"[ajouter à la bibliothèque](#ajouter-à-la-bibliothèque)\n"
": ajoutez des images existantes à la bibliothèque darktable sans copier ni déplacer de fichiers. Si vous n'ajoutez qu'une seule image à la bibliothèque, elle sera automatiquement ouverte dans la chambre noire.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[copy & import](#copy--import) \n"
": Create copies of images from the filesystem and then add those copies to the darktable library.\n"
msgstr ""
"[copier & importer...](#copy--import)\n"
": crée des copies d'images à partir du système de fichiers, puis ajoute ces copies à la bibliothèque darktable.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "When a camera is detected, a new section will appear in the module for that device. If you hover your mouse over the camera label, a tooltip will display information about the camera (model, firmware version etc.) \n"
msgstr "Lorsqu'un appareil photo est détecté, une nouvelle section apparaît pour cet appareil. Si vous passez la souris sur son nom, une info-bulle affiche des informations à son sujet (modèle, version du firmware, etc.) \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Depending on the capabilities of the camera, the following additional buttons may be displayed:\n"
msgstr "Selon les caractéristiques du boîtier, les boutons supplémentaires suivants peuvent s'afficher :\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mount camera\n"
": Mount the camera for exclusive use by darktable. This button only appears if the camera is not currently mounted and is not locked by another process.\n"
msgstr ""
"monter le boîtier\n"
": Monte le boîtier pour une utilisation exclusive par darktable. Ce bouton n'apparaît que si le boîtier n'est pas monté ni verrouillé par un autre processus.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[copy & import from camera](#copy--import-from-camera) \n"
": Create copies of images from the connected camera and then add those images to the darktable library. This button only appears if the camera is currently mounted.\n"
msgstr ""
"[copier & importer depuis le boîtier](#copy--import-from-camera) \n"
": crée des copies d'images à partir du boîtier connecté, puis ajoute ces images à la bibliothèque darktable. Ce bouton n'apparaît que si un boîtier est connecté.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[tethered shoot](../../../../tethering/_index.md) \n"
": Open the tethering view so that you can take images with your connected camera using darktable. This button only appears if the camera is currently mounted.\n"
msgstr ""
"[capture](../../../../tethering/_index.md)\n"
": Ouvre la vue capture afin de pouvoir prendre des images avec votre appareil photo connecté à l'aide de darktable. Ce bouton n'apparaît que si l'appareil est monté.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"unmount camera\n"
": Unmount the camera and release it for use by other applications. This button only appears if the camera is currently mounted.\n"
msgstr ""
"démonter le boîtier\n"
": Démonte le boîtier et le libère pour utilisation par d'autres applications. Ce bouton n'apparaît que si le boîtier est monté.\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "module parameters"
msgstr "paramètres du module"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Click on the \"parameters\" label or the expander button beside it to display the following additional options.\n"
msgstr "Cliquez sur l'étiquette « paramètres » ou sur le bouton d'extension à côté pour afficher les options supplémentaires suivantes.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "All parameters are retained from one session to the next and can be saved as module presets.\n"
msgstr "Tous les paramètres sont conservés d'une session à l'autre et peuvent être enregistrés dans un préréglage du module.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ignore exif rating\n"
": Check this option to ignore any rating stored within the image's Exif data and instead use a hard-coded value (below).\n"
msgstr ""
"ignorer la notation exif\n"
": cochez cette option pour ignorer toute évaluation enregistrée dans les données Exif de l'image et utiliser à la place une valeur codée en dur (ci-dessous).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"initial rating\n"
": Initial star rating (from 0 to 5) to use for all newly-imported images (default 1).\n"
msgstr ""
"notation initiale\n"
": Nombre d'étoiles initial (de 0 à 5) à appliquer aux images nouvellement importées (1 par défaut).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"apply metadata\n"
": Check this option to automatically set metadata fields and/or tags at import time (see below).\n"
msgstr ""
"appliquer métadonnées\n"
": Cochez cette option pour définir automatiquement les champs de métadonnées et/ou les balises au moment de l'importation (voir ci-dessous).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"metadata\n"
": If the \"apply metadata\" box is checked, a list of the _visible_ metadata fields is presented for completion (see [metadata editor](../shared/metadata-editor.md) for details). Any populated strings are automatically added to the imported images. You can also choose from any presets saved within the metadata editor module.\n"
msgstr ""
"métadonnées\n"
": Si la case \"appliquer les métadonnées\" est cochée, la liste des champs de métadonnées _visibles_ est présentée pour être complétée (voir [éditeur de métadonnées](../shared/metadata-editor.md) pour plus de détails). Toutes les chaînes remplies sont automatiquement ajoutées aux images importées. Vous pouvez également choisir parmi tous les préréglages enregistrés dans le module d'éditeur de métadonnées.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": Double-click on a label to reset the corresponding field. Double-click on the \"metadata presets\" label to reset all fields.\n"
msgstr ": Double-cliquez sur une étiquette pour réinitialiser le champ correspondant. Double-cliquez sur l'étiquette \"préréglages de métadonnées\" pour réinitialiser tous les champs.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": When [preferences > storage > write sidecar file for each image](../../../preferences-settings/storage.md#xmp) is unchecked an additional column \"from xmp\" is presented so that you can choose to prevent the import of metadata from XMP files.\n"
msgstr ": Lorsque [préférences > stockage > écrire un fichier xmp pour chaque image](../../../preferences-settings/storage.md#xmp) est décoché, une colonne supplémentaire \"depuis xmp\" est présentée afin que vous puissiez choisir pour empêcher l'importation de métadonnées à partir de fichiers XMP.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"tags\n"
": If you want to add further tags by default when importing images, you can provide them here as a comma separated list. As with metadata you can also choose from any presets saved within the [tagging](../shared/tagging.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""
"Mots clés\n"
": si vous souhaitez ajouter d'autres mots-clés par défaut lors de l'importation d'images, vous pouvez les fournir ici sous forme de liste, séparés par des virgules. Comme pour les métadonnées, vous pouvez également choisir parmi tous les préréglages enregistrés dans le module [mots-clés](../shared/tagging.md).\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "import dialog"
msgstr "la boîte de dialogue d'importation"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Each of the three import buttons (add to library, copy & import, copy & import from camera) uses a similar dialog for the import process, described in this section. \n"
msgstr "Chacun des trois boutons d'importation (ajouter à la bibliothèque, copier & importer, copier & importer depuis le boîtier) utilise une fenêtre de dialogue similaire pour le processus d'importation, décrit dans cette section. \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following example screenshot is taken from the \"add to library\" button:\n"
msgstr "L'exemple de capture d'écran suivant est tiré du bouton \"ajouter à la bibliothèque\" :\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "![import-dialog](./import/import-dialog.png#w100)\n"
msgstr "![dialogue d'importation](./import/import-dialog.png#w100)\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "common functionality"
msgstr "fonctionnalité commune"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "places and folders"
msgstr "emplacements et dossiers"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The import dialog is intended to allow you to set up common import locations, to make subsequent imports as simple as possible. When you first open the dialog, darktable attempts to add some common locations (home, pictures, mounted devices) to the places pane. You can add new places to the list by clicking on the + button and you can remove places from the list by right-clicking on them. If you wish to restore a default location that you have deleted, you can do this with the reset button.\n"
msgstr "La fenêtre de dialogue d'importation vous permet de configurer des emplacements d'importation communs, afin de rendre les importations ultérieures aussi simples que possible. Lorsque vous ouvrez la boîte de dialogue pour la première fois, darktable tente d'ajouter des emplacements communs (utilisateur, images, périphériques) dans le volet des emplacements. Vous pouvez ajouter de nouveaux emplacements à la liste en cliquant sur le bouton '+' et vous pouvez supprimer des lieux de la liste en faisant un clic droit dessus. Si vous souhaitez restaurer un emplacement par défaut que vous avez supprimé, vous pouvez le faire avec le bouton de réinitialisation.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "When you choose a place, the folder tree is automatically populated (into the folders pane) from the root directory of the selected place. You can then navigate the folder tree and select a folder for import. The last selected place/folder is automatically reloaded the next time you open the dialog.\n"
msgstr "Lorsque vous choisissez un emplacement, l'arborescence des dossiers est automatiquement renseignée (dans le volet dossiers) à partir de l'emplacement sélectionné. Vous pouvez ensuite parcourir l'arborescence des dossiers et sélectionner un dossier à importer. Le dernier dossier sélectionné est automatiquement affiché à l'ouverture de la fenêtre de dialogue.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the example screenshot above, you can see that a \"place\" has been created for the root of the Pictures folder and a sub-folder within that structure has been selected. This is the recommended workflow for the import process -- you should not have to create new places very often.\n"
msgstr "Dans l'exemple de capture d'écran ci-dessus, vous pouvez voir qu'un \"emplacement\" a été créé pour la racine du dossier Images et qu'un sous-dossier au sein de cette structure a été sélectionné. Il s'agit du flux de travail recommandé pour le processus d'importation -- vous ne devriez pas avoir à créer de nouveaux emplacements très souvent.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/collections.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "files"
msgstr "fichiers"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you have selected a folder, the files pane will automatically be populated with a list of the files found in that folder. By default, all files in the chosen folder are selected.\n"
msgstr "Une fois que vous avez sélectionné un dossier, le volet des fichiers est automatiquement rempli avec la liste des fichiers trouvés dans ce dossier. Par défaut, tous les fichiers du dossier choisi sont sélectionnés.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can view thumbnails for any of the images by clicking on the ![eye icon](./import/eye-icon.png#icon) icon. In addition, buttons are available at the bottom of the screen to select \"all\" files or \"none\".\n"
msgstr "Vous pouvez afficher les miniatures de n'importe quelle image en cliquant sur l'icône ![eye icon](./import/eye-icon.png#icon). Des boutons sont disponibles en bas de l'écran pour sélectionner tous les fichiers, \"tout sélectionner\" ou aucun, \"rien sélectionner\".\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you are happy with your selection, press Enter or click on the button at the bottom-right of the screen to import (this button will be named differently depending on the type of import being performed).\n"
msgstr "Quand vous êtes satisfait de votre sélection, appuyez sur Entrée ou cliquez sur le bouton en bas à droite de l'écran pour importer (ce bouton sera nommé différemment selon le type d'importation en cours).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Press Escape or click the \"cancel\" button to exit without importing.\n"
msgstr "Appuyez sur la touche Echap ou cliquez sur le bouton \"annuler\" pour quitter sans importer.\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "common options"
msgstr "options communes"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following additional options are common to all import dialogs:\n"
msgstr "Les options supplémentaires suivantes sont communes à toutes les boîtes de dialogue d'importation :\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"recursive directory\n"
": Check this option to import images in the selected folder _and all subfolders_. It is recommended that you not use this option to import a large number of images at the same time. The import process causes darktable to generate thumbnails for all of the imported images, but in the end it will only be able to keep the most recent in its cache. It is therefore better to import images in smaller chunks to avoid the performance penalty this imposes.\n"
msgstr ""
"récursivement\n"
": Cochez cette option pour importer des images dans le dossier sélectionné _et tous les sous-dossiers_. Il est déconseillé d'utiliser cette option pour importer un grand nombre d'images en même temps. Le processus d'importation amène darktable à générer des miniatures pour toutes les images importées, mais à la fin, il ne pourra conserver que les plus récentes dans son cache. Il est donc préférable d'importer des images en plusieurs fois pour éviter des problèmes de performance.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ignore JPEG images\n"
": Check this option if there are `JPEG` images in the same folder that you do not wish to import. This option is usually used where the camera stores `RAW+JPEG` and you only want to work on the `RAW` files, leaving the `JPEG` images untouched.\n"
msgstr ""
"ignorer les fichiers JPEG\n"
": Cochez cette option s'il y a des images `JPEG` dans le même dossier que vous ne souhaitez pas importer. Cette option est généralement utilisée lorsque l'appareil photo est configuré en `RAW+JPEG` et que vous souhaitez uniquement travailler sur les fichiers `RAW` et ignorer les fichiers `JPEG`.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "add to library"
msgstr "ajouter à la bibliothèque"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The \"add to library\" button allows you to add one or more existing images to the darktable library from the local filesystem. This process does not copy or move images but merely adds their details to the library database and creates XMP sidecar files for them.\n"
msgstr "Le bouton \"ajouter à la bibliothèque\" vous permet d'ajouter une ou plusieurs images à la bibliothèque darktable à partir du système de fichiers local. Ce processus ne copie ni ne déplace les images, mais les ajoute simplement à la bibliothèque et crée les fichiers annexes XMP.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select only new pictures\n"
": Tick this box to restrict the _initial_ selection (when the dialog is loaded) to only those images that have not already been loaded into the darktable library. If you attempt to reload existing images into the darktable library, data for those images will be reloaded from the XMP sidecar files. A button is also available at the bottom of the dialog to select only \"new\" images for the currently-selected folder.\n"
msgstr ""
"sélectionner seulement nouvelles images\n"
": Cochez cette case pour restreindre la sélection au chargement du dialogue aux images qui n'ont pas encore été incluses dans la bibliothèque darktable. Si vous essayez de recharger des images dans la bibliothèque darktable, les données associées sont lues des fichiers annexes XMP. Le bouton \"sélectionner nouveaux\" au bas de la boîte de dialogue sélectionne uniquement les \"nouvelles\" images pour le dossier courant.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Note:** \"Add to library\" does not create duplicates of your image files in a separate folder structure but processes them in-situ. The \"add to library\" process simply adds details of those images to darktable's library database (and creates an XMP sidecar file if applicable) allowing the images to be viewed and developed.\n"
msgstr "**Remarque :** \"ajouter à la bibliothèque\" ne crée pas de doublons de vos fichiers image dans une structure de dossiers distincte, mais les traite sur place. Le processus \"ajouter à la bibliothèque\" ajoute simplement les détails de ces images dans la bibliothèque de darktable (et crée un fichier annexe XMP le cas échéant) permettant aux images d'être visualisées et développées.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "This means that if you delete images from disk after having added them, darktable cannot access them any more. Moreover, darktable does not watch for changes in the filesystem. Any new images will not be shown until they are explicitly imported.\n"
msgstr "Cela signifie que si vous supprimez des images du disque après les avoir ajoutées, darktable ne peut plus y accéder. De plus, darktable ne surveille pas les changements dans le système de fichiers. Les nouvelles images ne sont pas affichées tant qu'elles ne sont pas explicitement importées.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "copy & import"
msgstr "copier & importer"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "This option copies images from another location on your filesystem (including mounted storage devices) and then adds the copied images to the darktable library. \n"
msgstr "Cette option copie les images d'un autre emplacement de votre système de fichiers (y compris les périphériques de stockage montés), puis ajoute les images copiées à la bibliothèque darktable. \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following additional options are available to control the file and directory naming of the copied files. By default, only the \"import job\" option is shown -- click on the \"naming rules\" label or the expander icon beside it to show additional options:\n"
msgstr "Les options supplémentaires suivantes sont disponibles pour définir le nom des répertoires et fichiers copiés. Par défaut, seule l'option _nom importation_ est affichée -- cliquez sur l'étiquette _règles de nommage_ ou sur l'icône d'extension à côté pour afficher des options supplémentaires :\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"import job\n"
": The name of the import job (populated into the `$(JOBCODE)` variable).\n"
msgstr ""
"nom importation\n"
": Le nom de la tâche d'importation (définit la variable `$(JOBCODE)`).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"override todays's date\n"
": Enter a valid date/time (in `YYYY-MM-DD[Thh:mm:ss]` format) if you want to override the current date/time used when expanding the variables `$(YEAR)`, `$(MONTH)`, `$(DAY)`, `$(HOUR)`, `$(MINUTE)` and `$(SECONDS)`. Leave the field empty otherwise.\n"
msgstr ""
"surcharger la date actuelle\n"
": Entrez une date/heure valide (au format `YYYY-MM-DD[Thh:mm:ss]`) si vous souhaitez remplacer la date/heure actuelle en provenance des variables `$(YEAR)`, `$(MONTH)`, `$(DAY)`, `$(HOUR)`, `$(MINUTE)` et `$(SECONDS)`. Sinon, laissez le champ vide.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"base directory naming pattern\n"
": The base directory part of the naming pattern (default `$(PICTURES_FOLDER)/Darktable`). Click on the icon beside the input field to choose a directory manually.\n"
msgstr ""
"modèle de nommage du répertoire de base\n"
": La partie répertoire de base du modèle de nommage (par défaut `$(PICTURES_FOLDER)/Darktable`). Cliquez sur l'icône à côté du champ de saisie pour choisir un répertoire manuellement.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#: content/preferences-settings/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sub directory naming pattern\n"
": The sub directory part of the naming pattern (default `$(YEAR)$(MONTH)$(DAY)_$(JOBCODE)`).\n"
msgstr ""
"modèle de nommage du sous répertoire\n"
": La partie sous-répertoire du modèle de nommage (par défaut `$(YEAR)$(MONTH)$(DAY)_$(JOBCODE)`).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"keep original filename\n"
": Check this box to keep original the filename instead of using the pattern below when importing.\n"
msgstr ""
"garder le nom d'origine\n"
": Cochez cette case pour conserver le nom de fichier d'origine au lieu d'utiliser le modèle ci-dessous lors de l'importation.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"file naming pattern\n"
": The file name part of the naming pattern (default `$(YEAR)$(MONTH)$(DAY)_$(SEQUENCE).$(FILE_EXTENSION)`).\n"
msgstr ""
"modèle de nommage du fichier\n"
": La partie nom du fichier du modèle de nommage (par défaut `$(YEAR)$(MONTH)$(DAY)_$(SEQUENCE).$(FILE_EXTENSION)`).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"keep this window open\n"
": Keep the window open after the import is complete, allowing multiple imports but with different naming options.\n"
msgstr ""
"garder cette fenêtre ouverte\n"
": laisse la fenêtre ouverte une fois l'importation terminée, permettant plusieurs importations avec différentes options de nommage.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Most of these options can also be set in [preferences > import](../../../../preferences-settings/import.md). See this section for more information about the available variables.\n"
msgstr "La plupart de ces options peuvent également être définies dans [préférences > importer](../../preferences-settings/import.md). Consultez cette section pour connaître les différentes variables possibles.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "copy & import from camera"
msgstr "copier& importer depuis le boîtier"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "This option copies files from a connected camera to the local filesystem and then adds the copied images to the darktable library. It provides the same naming options as the \"copy & import\" dialog but does not allow places or folders to be selected. \n"
msgstr "Cette option copie les fichiers d'un appareil photo connecté vers le système de fichiers local et ajoute ensuite les images copiées à la bibliothèque darktable. Elle fournit les mêmes options de nommage que la boîte de dialogue \"copier et importer\" mais ne permet pas la sélection d'emplacements ou de dossiers. \n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "select"
msgstr "sélectionner"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select images in the lighttable according to simple criteria.\n"
msgstr "Sélectionne des images dans la table lumineuse selon des critères simples.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select all\n"
": Select all images in the current collection.\n"
msgstr ""
"tout sélectionner\n"
": Sélectionne toutes les images de la collection courante.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select none\n"
": De-select all images.\n"
msgstr ""
"rien sélectionner\n"
": Désélectionne toutes les images.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"invert selection\n"
": Select all images in the current collection that are not currently selected.\n"
msgstr ""
"inverser la sélection\n"
": Sélectionne toutes les images non sélectionnées de la collection courante.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select film roll\n"
": Select all images in the current collection that are in the same film roll as the currently-selected images.\n"
msgstr ""
"dossier\n"
": Sélectionne toutes les images de la collection courante appartenant à la même pellicule que les images sélectionnées.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select untouched\n"
": Select all images in the current collection that have not yet been developed.\n"
msgstr ""
"non développées\n"
": Sélectionne toutes les images de la collection courante encore non développées.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/_index.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "map"
msgstr "carte"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "map settings"
msgstr "paramètres de carte"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select preferred map data from various providers. Some will provide additional layers (satellite view etc.) which you can toggle.\n"
msgstr "Permet de sélectionner les données cartographiques préférées parmi divers fournisseurs. Certains fournissent des couches supplémentaires (vue satellite, etc...).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"map source\n"
": Choose the provider to source map information from.\n"
msgstr ""
"source cartographique\n"
": Choisir le fournisseur d'informations cartographiques.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"max polygon points\n"
": The [find location](./find-location.md) module doesn't display polygons with more points than this for performance reasons. Usually a country polygon has between 50,000 and 150,000 points.\n"
msgstr ""
"max points polygone\n"
": Le module [trouver un lieu](./find-location.md) n'affiche pas les polygones avec plus de points que cette limite pour des raisons de performance. Habituellement un polygone de pays compte entre 50.000 et 150.000 points.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"show OSD\n"
": Choose whether to display the OSD controls at the top-left of the center view.\n"
msgstr ""
"afficher contrôles\n"
": Permet d'afficher les contrôles en haut à gauche de la vue centrale.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"filtered images\n"
": Check this box to display only the images from the current collection (those shown in the filmstrip) in the center view. Un-check the box to display all images in the current library, where those images have associated GPS data. You can also toggle this option by pressing Ctrl+S.\n"
msgstr ""
"images filtrées\n"
": Lorsque cette option est sélectionnée, seules les images de la pellicule (collection courante) s'affichent dans la vue centrale. Si elle n'est pas sélectionnée, toutes les images de la bibliothèque actuelle sont affichées si les images correspondantes sont associées à des données GPS. Vous pouvez aussi changer cette option en pressant Ctrl+S.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"max images\n"
": The maximum number of thumbnails to display on the map.\n"
msgstr ""
"max images\n"
": Le nombre maximum de miniatures affichées sur la carte.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"group size factor\n"
": Increase or decrease the size of area that causes images to be grouped.\n"
msgstr ""
"facteur de taille d'un groupe\n"
": Augmente ou diminue la zone d'influence du regroupement d'images.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"min images per group\n"
": The minimum number of images that need to be placed in the same position in order to automatically create an image group for them.\n"
msgstr ""
"nombre minimum d'images par groupe\n"
": Le nombre minimum d'images pour créer un groupe d'images.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"thumbnail display\n"
": Define what information to show on the map display\n"
": - _thumbnails_: Display image thumbnails along with a counter.\n"
": - _count_: Just display the number of images (to free space on the map). Hover over the number of images to show the corresponding thumbnail(s). A count-only marker behaves the same way as a normal image thumbnail, in terms of color coding, scrolling, drag and drop etc.\n"
": - _none_: Show nothing.\n"
": You can also cycle through these options by pressing Shift+S.\n"
msgstr ""
"affichage miniatures\n"
": Définit quelle information est affichée sur la carte\n"
": - _aperçu_ : Affiche la miniature des images ainsi qu'un compteur.\n"
": - _nombre_ : Affiche seulement le nombre d'images (pour libérer de l'espace sur la carte). Survoler le nombre d'images pour faire apparaître la (les) miniature(s) correspondante(s). Ce compteur se comporte de la même façon qu'un aperçu en termes de codage couleur, défilement, glisser déplacer, etc...\n"
": - _aucun_ : N'affiche rien.\n"
": Vous pouvez également changer en boucle ces options en appuyant sur Maj+S.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "locations"
msgstr "emplacements"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create areas or locations and organize them as hierarchical tags. \n"
msgstr "Créez des zones ou des emplacements et organisez-les sous forme de balises hiérarchiques. \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "A location is shown as a shape on the map when selected. Initially each location is represented as a square or circle and can be changed to a rectangle or ellipse by adjusting the shape's width and/or height.\n"
msgstr "Un emplacement est affiché sur la carte quand il est sélectionné. Initialement chaque emplacement est représenté par un carré ou un cercle, qui peut être changé en rectangle ou en ellipse en ajustant sa largeur et/ou sa hauteur.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "A location can also be created from an OpenStreetMap region (city/country) polygon. To achieve this, first make sure the _max polygon points_ parameter is large enough (some country polygons use more than 150,000 points). Then select the desired location in the [find location](./find-location.md) module. When the corresponding region shape is displayed, a polygon symbol becomes available in the \"shape\" control (see below). Select it to create the new location.\n"
msgstr "Un emplacement peut aussi être créé à partir d'un polygone représentant une région OpenStreetMap (ville/pays). Pour ce faire, assurez-vous que le paramètre _max points polygone_ est suffisamment grand (certains polygones de pays comptent plus de 150.000 points). Ensuite sélectionnez le lieu désiré dans le module [trouver un lieu](./find-location.md).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Each location is stored as tag entry under the geotagging collection in the [collections](../shared/collections.md) module. The pipe “|” character can be used to insert a new level (a group of locations).\n"
msgstr "Chaque emplacement est mémorisé en temps que mot-clé et peut être retrouvé dans la collection _géolocalisation_ du module [collections](../shared/collections.md). Le caractère tuyau \"|\" peut être utilisé pour insérer un niveau supplémentaire (un groupe d'emplacements).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shape\n"
": Select the circle or rectangle symbol to choose the default shape for new locations. A polygon symbol is available when a shape is displayed by the [find location](./find-location.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""
"forme\n"
": Sélectionner le symbole cercle ou rectangle pour choisir la forme par défaut des nouveaux emplacements. Un symbole polygone est disponible quand une forme (polygone) est affichée par le module [trouver un lieu](./find-location.md).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"new location / new sub-location\n"
": When no location is selected you can use the _new location_ button to create a location at root level. When a location is selected use the _new sub-location_ button to create a sub-location within the selected location.\n"
msgstr ""
"nouvel emplacement / nouveau sous-emplacement\n"
": Quand aucun emplacement n'est sélectionné vous pouvez utiliser le bouton _nouvel emplacement_ pour créer un emplacement au niveau racine. Quand un emplacement est sélectionné utilisez le bouton _sous-emplacement_ pour créer un sous-emplacement.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"show all\n"
": Show or hide all locations that lie within the visible area of the current map.\n"
msgstr ""
"tout montrer\n"
": Affiche ou cache tous les emplacements dans la zone visible de la carte.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "actions on the locations list"
msgstr "actions sur la liste des emplacements"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"click\n"
": Select or de-select a location. If the location is not currently visible on the map, the map is automatically centered on that location.\n"
msgstr ""
"clic\n"
": Sélectionne ou désélectionne un emplacement. Si l'emplacement n'est pas visible sur la carte, la carte est automatiquement centrée sur cet emplacement.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Ctrl+click\n"
": Edit the name of the location. Press Enter to save changes or Esc to close the editing window without saving.\n"
msgstr ""
"Ctrl+clic\n"
": Édite le nom de l'emplacement. Presser Entrée pour enregistrer les changements ou Echap pour fermer la fenêtre d'édition sans enregistrer.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"right-click\n"
": Open a sub-menu which allows you to:\n"
": - Edit the name of the location.\n"
": - Delete the location.\n"
": - Update the filmstrip -- the filmstrip will be populated with all images in the selected location.\n"
": - Switch to the lighttable view and show a collection that contains all images in the selected location.\n"
msgstr ""
"clic droit\n"
": Ouvre un sous menu qui vous permet de :\n"
": - Éditer le nom de l'emplacement\n"
": - Supprimer l'emplacement\n"
": - Mettre à jour la pellicule -- la pellicule est alors remplie de toutes les images de l'emplacement sélectionné. \n"
": - Basculer vers la vue table lumineuse et afficher la collection des images de l'emplacement sélectionné.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "actions on locations in the map"
msgstr "actions sur les emplacements sur la carte"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "_Note: The following actions have no effect on polygon locations._\n"
msgstr "_Note : Les actions suivantes n'ont pas d'effet sur les emplacements polygone._\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"click and drag\n"
": Move the location shape to a new position on the map.\n"
msgstr ""
"clic et déplacer\n"
": Déplace la forme de la localisation vers une nouvelle position sur la carte.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Ctrl+click or Ctrl+Shift+click\n"
": Move an image or a group of images and place them inside a location shape.\n"
msgstr ""
"Ctrl+clic ou Ctrl+Maj+clic\n"
": Déplace une image ou un groupe d'images à l'intérieur de la forme d'un emplacement.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mouse scroll\n"
": When inside a location shape (but not over an image), increase or decrease the size of that shape.\n"
": When hovering over an image, cycle through the thumbnails of images located at that position on the map.\n"
": When outside a location shape (and not over an image) zoom the map in or out.\n"
msgstr ""
"défilement souris\n"
": À l'intérieur d'un emplacement (mais pas au dessus d'une vignette), augmente ou diminue la taille de cette forme.\n"
": Au dessus d'une miniature, fait défiler les miniatures des images à cette position sur la carte.\n"
": En dehors d'un emplacement (et non au dessus d'une vignette) effectue zoom avant ou arrière de la carte.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Shift+scroll\n"
": Increase or decrease the width of the location shape.\n"
msgstr ""
"Maj+défilement\n"
": Augmente ou diminue la largeur de l'emplacement.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Ctrl+scroll\n"
": Increase or decrease the height of the location shape.\n"
msgstr ""
"Ctrl+défilement\n"
": Augmente ou diminue la hauteur de l'emplacement.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/locations.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"click on a location shape\n"
": Select a different location when the _show all_ checkbox is selected.\n"
msgstr ""
"clic sur une localisation\n"
": Sélectionne un emplacement différent lorsque _tout montrer_ est actif.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/find-location.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "find location"
msgstr "trouver un lieu"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/find-location.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Search for a location on the map. You must be connected to the internet to use this feature.\n"
msgstr "Trouver un lieu sur la carte. Vous devez être connecté à Internet pour utiliser cette fonction.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/find-location.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "To use this module, type in a place name or address, press Enter and a list of results will be shown. Click on an item in the list and the map will zoom to that location. An outline covering that location or a pin pointing at the location will be displayed.\n"
msgstr "Pour utiliser ce module, tapez un nom de lieu ou une adresse, appuyez sur Entrée et une liste de résultats s'affichera. Cliquez sur un élément de la liste et la carte s'agrandira jusqu'à ce lieu. Un contour couvrant ce lieu ou une épingle pointant vers ce lieu s'affiche.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/find-location.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "An outline (polygon) can be used to create a user location. Check the _max polygon points_ parameter in the [map settings](./map-settings.md) module to ensure that sufficient points are available for a polygon to be displayed.\n"
msgstr "Un contour (polygone) peut être utilisé pour créer un emplacement utilisateur. Vérifiez le paramètre _max points polygone_ dans le module [paramètres de carte](./map-settings.md) pour vous assurer que suffisamment de points sont disponibles pour qu'un polygone soit affiché.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/_index.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "print"
msgstr "impression"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "print settings"
msgstr "paramètres d'impression"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manage settings for the [print view](../../../print/_index.md) and initiate printing.\n"
msgstr "Gérer les paramètre de la [vue impression](../../../print/_index.md) et lancer l'impression.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "printer"
msgstr "imprimante"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"printer\n"
": Select one of the installed printers.\n"
msgstr ""
"imprimante\n"
": Sélectionner l'une des imprimantes installées.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"media\n"
": The type of media loaded on the printer (Plain Paper, Luster Photo Paper, etc.).\n"
msgstr ""
"type de papier\n"
": Le type de papier de l'imprimante (papier ordinaire, papier photo lustré, etc.).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"profile\n"
": The printer's ICC profile for the loaded paper. This is the profile specific to the printer and paper. This profile is the last color space transformation applied to the picture whose goal is to create a high quality print.\n"
msgstr ""
"profil\n"
": Le profil ICC de l'imprimante pour le papier chargé. C'est le profil spécifique à l'imprimante et au papier de l'imprimante. L'application de ce profil est la dernière transformation d'espace colorimétrique faite à l'image. Son but est de créer une impression de haute qualité.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"intent\n"
": The print rendering intent (“perceptual”, “relative colorimetric”, “saturation” or “absolute colorimetric”). See [rendering intent](../../../special-topics/color-management/rendering-intent.md) for more details.\n"
msgstr ""
"rendu\n"
": L'intention de rendu pour l'impression (\"perceptif\", \"colorimétrie relative\", \"saturation\" ou \"colorimétrie absolue\"). Voir [intention de rendu](../../../special-topics/color-management/rendering-intent.md) pour plus de détails.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"black point compensation\n"
": Whether to adjust the black point of the output profile, which is often lighter than the input profile. This should be “on” when the _intent_ is set to “relative colorimetric”.\n"
msgstr ""
"compensation du point noir\n"
": Le point noir du profil de sortie, qui est souvent plus clair que celui du profil d'entrée, sera ajusté quand la case est cochée . Elle devrait l'être si le paramètre _rendu_ ci-dessus est fixé à “colorimétrie relative”.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "page"
msgstr "page"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"paper size\n"
": The size of the paper on which to print.\n"
msgstr ""
"taille papier\n"
": La taille du papier pour l'impression.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"orientation\n"
": Portrait or landscape (note that darktable chooses the best fit by default).\n"
msgstr ""
"orientation\n"
": Portrait ou paysage (notez que darktable choisit par défaut la meilleure solution).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"units\n"
": The unit to use for setting the margins: “mm”, “cm”, or “inch”.\n"
msgstr ""
"unités\n"
": L'unité à utiliser pour régler les marges : mm, cm, et pouce sont les options disponibles.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"margins\n"
": Set each margin separately, or all together by clicking on the middle “lock” button.\n"
msgstr ""
"marges\n"
": Il est possible de régler séparément chaque marge ou de toutes les régler simultanément en cliquant le bouton « sync » central.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"display grid\n"
": Select the grid size using the entry field (expressed in the currently selected unit). Tick the option to display the grid on the canvas.\n"
msgstr ""
"afficher la grille\n"
": Sélectionnez la taille de la grille à l'aide du champ de saisie (exprimée dans l'unité actuellement sélectionnée). Cochez pour afficher la grille sur le canevas.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"snap to grid\n"
": Help setting the image areas by snapping them to the grid for proper alignment.\n"
msgstr ""
"aligner sur la grille\n"
": aide à définir les zones de l'image en les accrochant à la grille pour un alignement correct.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"borderless mode required\n"
": Indicates whether the printer borderless mode is to be activated. This item is activated when the user's margins are smaller than the printer hardware margins. Note that it is only an indicator as it does not activate the borderless mode automatically.\n"
msgstr ""
"mode sans bordure requis\n"
": Lorsque les marges de l'utilisateur sont inférieures aux marges matérielles de l'imprimante, cet élément est activé (il n'est plus grisé). Il indique alors que le mode sans bordure de l'imprimante doit être activé. Notez qu'il ne s'agit que d'un indicateur car il n'active pas automatiquement le mode sans bordure.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "image layout"
msgstr "disposition des images"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"image width/height\n"
": This information field displays the actual image width and height (given with the selected units) on the paper.\n"
msgstr ""
"largeur/hauteur image\n"
": Ce champ d'informations affiche les largeur et hauteur réelle de l'image sur le papier (données avec les unités sélectionnées).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"scale factor\n"
": This information field displays the scaling of the image to fit on the paper. If this value is less than 1 the image is down-scaled, otherwise it is up-scaled. This is an important factor to watch -- a value that is too large (up-scale) may result in a low quality print. The corresponding dpi (dots per inch) is also displayed.\n"
msgstr ""
"facteur d’agrandissement\n"
": Ce champ d'informations affiche le facteur d'agrandissement de l'image nécessaire à son ajustement à la taille du papier. Si cette valeur est inférieure à 1 l'image est réduite sinon elle est agrandie. C'est un important facteur à surveiller -- une trop grande valeur (agrandissement) peut produire une impression de qualité médiocre. Le dpi (nombre de points par pouce ; dots per inch en anglais) est aussi affiché.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"alignment\n"
": Select the alignment of the image on its area.\n"
msgstr ""
"alignement\n"
": Sélectionnez l'alignement de l'image sur sa zone.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"new image area button\n"
": Create a new image area. Drag and drop on the canvas to place it. If the option snap to grid is activated the area can be easily aligned to the grid lines. An image can be placed into this area by dragging it from the filmstrip and dropping it on the new area.\n"
msgstr ""
"nouvelle zone image\n"
": Créer une nouvelle zone image. Glissez-déposez sur le canevas pour la placer. Si l'option aligner sur la grille est activée, la zone peut être facilement alignée sur les lignes de la grille. Une image peut être placée dans cette zone en la faisant glisser depuis la pellicule et en la déposant sur la nouvelle zone.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"delete image area button\n"
": Remove the currently selected image area from the composition.\n"
msgstr ""
"supprimer zone image\n"
": Supprime de la composition la zone image actuellement sélectionnée.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"clear layout button\n"
": Remove all the image areas leaving the canvas empty.\n"
msgstr ""
"effacer composition\n"
": Supprime toutes les zones image en laissant le canevas vide.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following four fields represent the position of currently selected area on the page -- the top/left corner on the first line and the width/height of the area on the second line.\n"
msgstr "Les quatre champs suivants représentent la position de la zone actuellement sélectionnée sur la page -- le coin supérieur/gauche sur la première ligne et la largeur/hauteur de la zone sur la deuxième ligne.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "When hovering an image area its position and size are displayed. It is also possible to grab the side and corner of the area to change the size or to drag the whole area to change its position.\n"
msgstr "Lorsque vous survolez une zone image, sa position et sa taille sont affichées. Il est également possible de saisir le côté et le coin de la zone pour changer la taille ou de faire glisser toute la zone pour changer sa position.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The page layout can be recorded using a preset.\n"
msgstr "La mise en page peut être enregistrée à l'aide d'un préréglage.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"profile\n"
": The export profile to use. This profile is the entry point used for the next transformation using the printer's ICC profile. Usually it is better to prefer a large gamut (e.g. Adobe RGB) rather than a smaller one (e.g. sRGB).\n"
msgstr ""
"profil\n"
": Ceci vous permet de sélectionner le profil d'exportation à utiliser. Ce profil est le point d'entrée utilisé par la prochaine transformation utilisant le profil d'imprimante ICC ci-dessus. Habituellement il est préférable d'utiliser un profil avec un grand gamut comme AdobeRVB plutôt qu'un profil avec un gamut plus petit comme sRVB.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"intent\n"
": The rendering intent to use when exporting the image. For more information see [rendering intent](../../../special-topics/color-management/rendering-intent.md).\n"
msgstr ""
"rendu\n"
": Cette option fixe l'intention de rendu à utiliser pour l'exportation de l'image. Pour plus de d'informations voir [intention de rendu](../../../special-topics/color-management/rendering-intent.md).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"style\n"
": Choose a style to apply when exporting the image -- defaults to “none”. See the [export](../shared/export.md) module for a more detailed discussion of applying a style during export.\n"
msgstr ""
"style\n"
": Définit le style à appliquer lors de l'exportation de l'image, la valeur par défaut est « sans ». Voyez le panneau [exportation](../shared/export.md) pour une discussion plus détaillée de l'application d'un style lors de l'exportation.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mode\n"
": Whether the chosen style should be appended to the existing history stack or replace it completely. See the [export](../shared/export.md) module for more details.\n"
msgstr ""
"mode\n"
": Indique si le style sera ajouté à l'historique existant ou s'il le remplacera complètement. Voir [exportation](../shared/export.md) pour plus de détails.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "print button"
msgstr "bouton d'impression"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, no-wrap
