#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `darktable-chart` binary is a dedicated utility to create styles out of pairs of images such as RAW+JPEG with in-camera processing. Details about its usage can be found in the [using darktable-chart](../darktable-chart/_index.md) section.\n"
msgstr "Cet exécutable est un utilitaire dédié à la création de styles à partir de paires d'images telles que RAW+JPEG fournies par le boîtier. Des détails de son utilisation peuvent être trouvés dans la section [utiliser darktable-chart](../darktable-chart/_index.md)\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`darktable-chart` can either start a GUI or be used as a command-line program.\n"
msgstr "`darktable-chart` soit démarre une interface graphique soit est utilisé comme programme en ligne de commande.\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"darktable-chart\n"
"              [--help]\n"
"              [<input Lab pfm file>]\n"
"              [<cht file>]\n"
"              [<reference cgats/it8 or Lab pfm file>]\n"
msgstr ""
"darktable-chart\n"
"              [--help]\n"
"              [<input Lab pfm file>]\n"
"              [<cht file>]\n"
"              [<reference cgats/it8 or Lab pfm file>]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "All parameters are optional, however, if you want to supply the second file name you also need to supply the first one. Starting `darktable-chart` this way opens a special GUI (details can be found in the [using darktable-chart](../darktable-chart/_index.md) section).\n"
msgstr "Tous les paramètres sont optionnels, cependant, si vous voulez fournir le deuxième nom de fichier vous devez aussi fournir le premier. Démarrer `darktable-chart` de cette manière ouvre une interface graphique spéciale (des détails peuvent être trouvés dans la section [utiliser darktable-chart](../darktable-chart/_index.md)).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--help`\n"
": Provide usage information and terminate.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--help`\n"
": Donne des informations d'utilisation et s'arrête.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`<input Lab pfm file>`\n"
": Open the utility with the given file as source image. The input file needs to be in Lab Portable Float Map format.\n"
msgstr ""
"`<input Lab pfm file>`\n"
": Ouvre l'utilitaire avec le fichier donné comme image source. Le fichier en entrée doit être au format Lab Portable Float Map.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`<cht file>`\n"
": Specify a chart file describing the layout of the used color reference chart.\n"
msgstr ""
"`<cht file>`\n"
": Spécifie un fichier décrivant la disposition du diagramme de références couleur.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`<reference cgats/it8 or Lab pfm file>`\n"
": Specify the reference values, either as measured values according to the CGATS standard, or as a reference image in Lab Portable Float Map format.\n"
msgstr ""
"`<reference cgats/it8 or Lab pfm file>`\n"
": Spécifie les valeurs de référence, soit comme valeurs mesurées en fonction du standard CGATS, soit comme image de référence dans le format Lab Portable Float Map.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternatively `darktable-chart` can be used as a command line program to generate darktable style files using previously saved CSV files.\n"
msgstr "Alternativement `darktable-chart` peut être utilisé comme un programme en ligne de commande pour générer des fichiers de style en utilisant des fichiers CVS précédemment sauvegardés.\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"darktable-chart\n"
"              --csv\n"
"              <csv file>\n"
"              <number patches>\n"
"              <output dtstyle file>\n"
msgstr ""
"darktable-chart\n"
"              --csv\n"
"              <csv file>\n"
"              <number patches>\n"
"              <output dtstyle file>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "All parameters are mandatory.\n"
msgstr "Tous les paramètres sont obligatoires.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`<csv file>`\n"
": A CSV file previously saved from within `darktable-chart`.\n"
msgstr ""
"`<csv file>`\n"
": Un fichier CSV précédemment sauvegardé avec `darktable-chart`.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`<number of patches>`\n"
": The number of color patches to be used in the color look up table settings of the created style.\n"
msgstr ""
"`<number of patches>`\n"
": Le nombre de pastilles de couleur à utiliser dans le paramétrage de la table correspondance couleurs du style créé.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-chart.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`<output dtstyle file>`\n"
": The name of the style file to be created.\n"
msgstr ""
"`<output dtstyle file>`\n"
": Nom du fichier de style qui doit être créé.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "darktable-cli"
msgstr "darktable-cli"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `darktable-cli` binary starts the command line interface variant of darktable which allows images to be exported.\n"
msgstr "L'exécutable `darktable-cli` lance la variante en ligne de commande de l’interface de darktable qui permet l’exportation d’images.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "This variant does not open any display -- it works in pure console mode without launching a GUI. This mode is particularly useful for servers running background jobs.\n"
msgstr "Cette variante n'ouvre aucun affichage -- elle travaille en mode console pur sans lancer d'interface graphique. Ce mode est particulièrement utile pour les serveurs exécutant des tâches en arrière-plan.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`darktable-cli` can be called with the following command line parameters:\n"
msgstr "`darktable-cli` peut être appelé avec les paramètres suivants de la ligne de commande :\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"darktable-cli [<input file or folder>]\n"
"              [<xmp file>]\n"
"              <output file or folder>\n"
"              [--width <max width>]\n"
"              [--height <max height>]\n"
"              [--bpp <bpp>]\n"
"              [--hq <0|1|true|false>]\n"
"              [--upscale <0|1|true|false>]\n"
"              [--style <style name>]\n"
"              [--style-overwrite]\n"
"              [--apply-custom-presets <0|1|false|true>]\n"
"              [--out-ext <extension>]\n"
"              [--import <file or dir>]\n"
"              [--icc-type <type>]\n"
"              [--icc-file <file>]\n"
"              [--icc-intent <intent>]\n"
"              [--verbose]\n"
"              [--help [option]]\n"
"              [--core <darktable options>]\n"
msgstr ""
"darktable-cli [<input file or folder>]\n"
"              [<xmp file>]\n"
"              <output file or folder>\n"
"              [--width <max width>]\n"
"              [--height <max height>]\n"
"              [--bpp <bpp>]\n"
"              [--hq <0|1|true|false>]\n"
"              [--upscale <0|1|true|false>]\n"
"              [--style <style name>]\n"
"              [--style-overwrite]\n"
"              [--apply-custom-presets <0|1|false|true>]\n"
"              [--out-ext <extension>]\n"
"              [--import <file or dir>]\n"
"              [--icc-type <type>]\n"
"              [--icc-file <file>]\n"
"              [--icc-intent <intent>]\n"
"              [--verbose]\n"
"              [--help [option]]\n"
"              [--core <darktable options>]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The user must supply an input filename and an output filename. All other parameters are optional.\n"
msgstr "L’utilisateur doit fournir un nom de fichier d’entrée et un nom de fichier de sortie. Tous les autres paramètres sont optionnels.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`<input file or folder>`\n"
": The name of the input file or folder (containing images) to be exported. If you wish to process multiple images or multiple folders use the `--import` option instead.\n"
msgstr ""
"`<input file or folder>`\n"
": Le nom du fichier en entrée ou du répertoire (contenant des images) à exporter. Si vous souhaitez développer plusieurs images ou plusieurs répertoires utilisez plutôt l'option `--import`.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`<xmp file>`\n"
": The optional name of an XMP sidecar file containing the history stack data to be applied during export. If this option is not provided darktable will search for an XMP file that belongs to the given input file(s).\n"
msgstr ""
"`<xmp file>`\n"
": Nom optionnel d’un fichier lié XMP qui contient les données de l’historique de développement qui sera appliqué lors de l’exportation. Si cette option n’est pas donnée, darktable recherchera un fichier XMP appartenant au(x) fichier(s) d’entrée indiqué(s).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`<output file or folder>`\n"
": The name of the output file or destination folder. The export file format is derived from the file extension or from the `--out-ext` option. You can also use a number of [variables](../variables.md) in the output filename. For obvious reasons this parameter is mandatory if you use the program on an image folder containing multiple images. If you specify output folder it is recommended that you also specify the file format with `--out-ext`.\n"
msgstr ""
"`<output file or folder>`\n"
": Le nom du fichier de sortie ou le répertoire de destination. Le format du fichier de sortie est dérivé de son extension ou de l'option `--out-ext` . Vous pouvez aussi utiliser des [variables de substitution](../variables.md) dans le nom du fichier de sortie. Pour des raisons évidentes ceci est obligatoire si vous utilisez le programme pour un répertoire contenant de nombreuses images. Si vous spécifiez le répertoire de sortie, il est recommandé de spécifier également le format de fichier avec `--out-ext`.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--width <max width>`\n"
": Limit the width of the exported image to the given number of pixels.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--width <max width>`\n"
": Ce paramètre permet de limiter la largeur de l’image exportée au nombre de pixels indiqué.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--height <max height>`\n"
": Limit the height of the exported image to the given number of pixels.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--height <max height>`\n"
": Ce paramètre permet de limiter la hauteur de l’image exportée au nombre de pixels indiqué.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--bpp <bpp>`\n"
": Define the bit depth of the exported image. Permitted values depend on the output file format. \n"
msgstr ""
"`--bpp <bpp>`\n"
": Ce paramètre définit la profondeur de bits de l’image exportée. Les valeurs autorisées dépendent du format de fichier. \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Note:** This option is not currently functional. If you need to define the bit depth you need to use the following workaround:\n"
msgstr "**Remarque** Actuellement, cette option n’est pas encore fonctionnelle. Si vous devez définir la profondeur de bits, vous devez utiliser la solution suivante :\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    --core\n"
"    --conf plugins/imageio/format/<FORMAT>/bpp=<VALUE>\n"
msgstr ""
"    --core\n"
"    --conf plugins/imageio/format/<FORMAT>/bpp=<VALUE>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "where `<FORMAT>` is the name of the selected output format.\n"
msgstr "où`<FORMAT>` est le nom du format de sortie sélectionné.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--hq <0|1|true|false>`\n"
": Define whether to use high quality resampling during export (see the [export](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/export.md) module reference for more details). Defaults to true.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--hq <0|1|true|false>`\n"
": Définit s’il faut utiliser un ré-échantillonnage de haute qualité lors de l’exportation (voir le module [exporter sélection](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/export.md) pour plus de détails). Vrai par défaut.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--upscale <0|1|true|false>`\n"
": Define whether allow upscaling during export. Defaults to false.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--upscale <0|1|true|false>`\n"
": Indicateur définissant s’il faut utiliser un ré-échantillonnage de haute qualité lors de l’exportation Faux par défaut.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--style <style name>`\n"
": Specify the name of a style to be applied during export. If a style is specified, the path to the darktable configuration directory must also be specified (i.e. `--core --configdir ~/.config/darktable`). By default no style is applied.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--style <style name>`\n"
": Spécifiez le nom d'un style à appliquer lors de l'exportation. Si un style est spécifié, le chemin d'accès au répertoire de configuration darktable doit également être spécifié (c'est-à-dire `--core --configdir ~/.config/darktable`). Par défaut, aucun style n'est spécifié.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--style-overwrite`\n"
": The specified style overwrites the history stack instead of being appended to it.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--style-overwrite`\n"
": Le style spécifié remplace l'historique au lieu d'y être ajouté.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--apply-custom-presets <0|1|false|true>`\n"
": Whether to load `data.db` which contains presets and styles. Disabling this option allows you to run multiple instances of `darktable-cli` at the cost of being unable to use the `--style` option. Defaults to true.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--apply-custom-presets <0|1|false|true>`\n"
": S'il faut charger `data.db` qui contient des préréglages et des styles. Désactiver cette option vous permet de lancer plusieurs instances de `darktable-cli` au prix de ne pas pouvoir utiliser l'option `--style`. La valeur par défaut est vrai.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--out-ext <extension>`\n"
": Set the output extension to use. If specified takes precedence over `<output file>`. By default this is extracted from `<output file>`. Defaults to `jpg` if `<output folder>` is specified.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--out-ext <extension>`\n"
": Définissez l'extension de sortie à utiliser. Si elle est spécifiée, elle est prioritaire sur celle du `<fichier de sortie>`. Par défaut, elle est extraite du nom du `<fichier de sortie>`. La valeur par défaut est `jpg` si un ` <répertoire de sortie> `est spécifié.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--import <file or dir>`\n"
": Specify input file or folder, can be used multiple times. This option cannot be combined with `<input file or folder>`.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--import <file or dir>`\n"
": Spécifiez le fichier ou le répertoire d'entrée, peut être utilisé plusieurs fois. Cette option ne peut pas être combinée avec `<input file or folder>`.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--icc-type <type>`\n"
": Specify the ICC profile type, which is the same as specifying the \"output profile\" in the [_output color profile_](../../module-reference/processing-modules/output-color-profile.md) module. Defaults to \"image specified\". Use `--help icc-type` to obtain a list of the supported types. See the _output color profile_ module reference for a more detailed description of the available options.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--icc-type <type>`\n"
": Spécifiez le type de profil ICC, ce qui revient à spécifier le \"profil de sortie\" dans le module _profil de couleur de sortie_. La valeur par défaut est \"image spécifiée\". Utilisez`--help icc-type` pour obtenir une liste des types pris en charge. Voir [profil couleur de sortie](../../module-reference/processing-modules/output-color-profile) pour une description plus détaillée des options disponibles.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--icc-file <file>` \n"
": Specify the ICC profile filename. Defaults to an empty filename.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--icc-file <file>`\n"
": Spécifiez le nom de fichier du profil ICC. Par défaut, un nom de fichier vide.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--icc-intent <intent>` \n"
": Specify the rendering intent. Defaults to \"image specified\". Use `--help icc-intent` to obtain a list of the supported intents. See [rendering intent](../../special-topics/color-management/rendering-intent) for a more detailed description of the available options.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--icc-intent <intent>`\n"
": Spécifiez l'intention de rendu. Utilisez `--help icc-intent` pour obtenir une liste des modes de rendu pris en charge. Voir [intention de rendu](../../special-topics/color-management/rendering-intent) pour une description plus détaillée des options disponibles.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--verbose`\n"
": Enables verbose output.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--verbose`\n"
": Activer la sortie verbeuse.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--help [option]`\n"
": Prints usage and exits. If `option` is specified, additionally prints usage for the given option.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--help [option]`\n"
": Donne les paramètres d'usage et quitte. Si `option` est spécifié, donne en plus les paramètres de l'option donnée.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cli.md
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--core <darktable options>`\n"
": All command line parameters following `--core` are passed to the darktable core and handled as standard parameters. See the [`darktable binary`](./darktable.md) section for a detailed description.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--core <darktable options>`\n"
": Tous les paramètres de la ligne de commande suivant `--core` sont passés au noyau de darktable et manipulés comme des paramètres standards. Voir la section [_Exécutable darktable_](./darktable.md) pour une description détaillée.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cltest.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "darktable-cltest"
msgstr "darktable-cltest"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cltest.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `darktable-cltest` binary checks if there is a usable OpenCL environment on your system that darktable can use. It emits some debug output that is equivalent to calling `darktable -d opencl` and then terminates.\n"
msgstr "L'exécutable `darktable-cltest` vérifie s'il y a sur votre système un environnement OpenCL utilisable par darktable. Il émet une sortie de débogage équivalente à celle qu'on obtient par l'appel `darktable -d opencl` et puis s'arrête.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cltest.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`darktable-cltest` is called without command line parameters.\n"
msgstr "`darktable-cltest` est appelé sans paramètre sur la ligne de commande.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cmstest.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "darktable-cmstest"
msgstr "darktable-cmstest"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cmstest.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `darktable-cmstest` binary (Linux only) investigates whether the color management subsystem of your computer is correctly configured and displays some useful information about the installed monitor profile(s).\n"
msgstr "L'exécutable `darktable-cmstest` (sous Linux uniquement) détermine si le sous-système de votre ordinateur gérant la couleur est correctement configuré et affiche des informations utiles sur le(s) profil(s)-moniteur installé(s) .\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-cmstest.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`darktable-cmstest` is called without command line parameters.\n"
msgstr "`darktable-cmstest` est appelé sans paramètre sur la ligne de commande.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "darktable-generate-cache"
msgstr "darktable-generate-cache"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `darktable-generate-cache` binary updates darktable's thumbnail cache. Invoke this program to generate all missing thumbnails in the background when your computer is idle.\n"
msgstr "L'exécutable `darktable-generate-cache` met à jour le cache des miniatures. Vous pouvez lancer ce programme, en arrière-plan quand votre ordinateur est inactif, pour générer toutes les miniatures manquantes .\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`darktable-generate-cache` can be called with the following command line parameters:\n"
msgstr "`darktable-generate-cache` est appelé avec les paramètres suivants de la ligne de commande :\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"darktable-generate-cache\n"
"              [-h, --help]\n"
"              [--version]\n"
"              [--min-mip <0-8>] [-m, --max-mip <0-8>]\n"
"              [--min-imgid <N>] [--max-imgid <N>]\n"
"              [--core <darktable options>]\n"
msgstr ""
"darktable-generate-cache\n"
"              [-h, --help]\n"
"              [--version]\n"
"              [--min-mip <0-8>] [-m, --max-mip <0-8>]\n"
"              [--min-imgid <N>] [--max-imgid <N>]\n"
"              [--core <darktable options>]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "All parameters are optional. If started without parameters `darktable-generate-cache` uses reasonable defaults.\n"
msgstr "Tous les paramètres sont optionnels. S'il est démarré sans paramètre `darktable-generate-cache` utilise des valeurs par défaut raisonnables.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`-h, --help`\n"
": Display usage information and terminate.\n"
msgstr ""
"`-h, --help`\n"
": Donne des informations d'utilisation et s'arrête.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--version`\n"
": Display copyright and version information and terminate.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--version`\n"
": Donne des informations de version et de copyright et s'arrête.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--min-mip <0-8>, -m, --max-mip <0-8>`\n"
": darktable can store thumbnails with up to eight different resolution steps for each image. These parameters define the maximum resolution to be generated (defaults to a range of 0-2). There is normally no need to generate all possible resolutions here -- missing ones will be automatically generated by darktable the moment they are needed. When asked to generate multiple resolutions at once, the lower-resolution images are quickly downsampled from the highest-resolution image.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--min-mip <0 - 8>, -m, --max-mip <0 - 8>`\n"
": darktable peut gérer et stocker, pour chaque image, des miniatures ayant jusqu'à huit niveaux différents de résolution. Ces paramètres définissent la résolution maximale qui doit être générée (valeur par défaut dans une plage de 0 à 2). Il n'est normalement pas nécessaire de générer ici toutes les résolutions possibles ; celles qui manquent seront générées automatiquement par darktable au moment où elles seront nécessaires. Quand on demande la génération de plusieurs résolutions à la fois, les images de plus basse résolution sont rapidement sous-échantillonnées à partir de l'image de la plus haute résolution.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`--min-imgid <N>, --max-imgid <N>`\n"
": Specifies the range of internal image IDs from the database to work on. If no range is given, `darktable-generate-cache` will process all images.\n"
msgstr ""
"`--min-imgid <N>, --max-imgid <N>`\n"
": Spécifie la plage d'IDs des images de la base de données sur laquelle il faut travailler. Si aucune plage n'est donnée, `darktable-generate-cache` générera le cache de toutes les images de la collection.\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "purge_non_existing_images.sh"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Find and remove entries from the library database referencing images that no longer exist in the filesystem. You must close darktable before running this script.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The script can be called with the following command line parameters:\n"
msgstr "Le script peut être appelé avec les paramètres suivants de la ligne de commande :\n"

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"purge_non_existing_images.sh [-c|--configdir <path>]\n"
"                             [-l|--library <path>]\n"
"                             [-p|--purge]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Run the script with no options to perform a \"dry run\", which generates a report of the missing files without committing any changes to the database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The available options are:\n"
msgstr "Les options disponibles sont :\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`-c|--configdir <path>`\n"
": Specify the path to the darktable configuration directory to be used by the script. If this option is not provided, the default config directory location will be used.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`-l|--library <path>`\n"
": Specify the path to the library.db database file to be analysed by the script. If this option is not specified, the default library.db file location will be used.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`-p|--purge`\n"
": Actually delete any entries in the database that refer to non-existent files. If the option is not provided, a report will be printed without committing any changes to the database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Notes:**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The script must be run in a unix shell, and the `sqlite3` client must be available in the command search path. For Linux systems, this will normally not be an issue. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "For Windows systems, you will normally need the MSYS2 environment to be installed, as described in the [instructions for building darktable in a Windows environment](https://github.com/darktable-org/darktable/blob/master/packaging/windows/BUILD.md). If you installed darktable using the standard Windows installer package, the location of the script would normally be something like: `C:\\Program Files\\darktable\\share\\darktable\\tools\\purge_non_existing_images.sh`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "For macOS systems, the Terminal application provides a shell, and the `sqlite3` client is provided by the operating system by default. If darktable was installed using an application bundle from a dmg image, then the default location for the script would be `/Applications/darktable.app/Contents/Resources/share/darktable/tools/purge_non_existing_images.sh`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The delete operation can't be undone. It is therefore strongly recommended that you take a backup of the database before purging any entries.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `darktable` binary starts darktable with its GUI and full functionality. This is the standard way to use darktable.\n"
msgstr "Le binaire `darktable` démarre darktable avec son interface graphique et ses fonctionnalités complètes. C'est la manière standard d'utiliser darktable.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/program-invocation/darktable.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "`darktable` can called with the following command line parameters:\n"
msgstr "`darktable` peut être appelé avec les paramètres de ligne de commande suivants :\n"

