msgid "general style guidance"
msgstr "conseils généraux de style"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "All content should be authored in plain markdown without shortcodes and HTML should be kept to an absolute minimum , if used at all\n"
msgstr "Tout le contenu doit être rédigé en clair sans code abrégé et le HTML doit être réduit au minimum absolu, s'il est utilisé.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Minimalism is an absolute must. Fewer words are preferred\n"
msgstr "Le minimalisme est un must absolu. Le moins de mots possible est préféré\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Markdown files should be as short as possible\n"
msgstr "Les fichiers Markdown doivent être aussi courts que possible\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Follow the naming and capitalization norms present in the GUI of the application -- namely all headers and titles are in lower case, except for the very top-level chapter names\n"
msgstr "Suivez les normes de dénomination et de capitalisation présentes dans l'interface graphique de l'application -- à savoir que tous les en-têtes et titres sont en minuscules, à l'exception des noms de chapitre de très haut niveau\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Headers in a file should not exceed level three (###)\n"
msgstr "Les en-têtes dans un fichier ne doivent pas dépasser le niveau trois (###)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The primary authoring language is English\n"
msgstr "La langue de création principale est l'anglais\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assume the reader has the application open while reading the user manual and only include images where they contribute to the explanation of complex functionality\n"
msgstr "Supposez que le lecteur a ouvert l'application lors de la lecture du manuel d'utilisation et n'incluez que des images où elles contribuent à l'explication de fonctionnalités complexes\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use image callouts if you need to annotate an image (i.e. mark parts of the image with a letter or number and then explain the meaning in some text following the image). Do not place words directly into the image for annotations, as this makes localization difficult. See [this page](../darkroom/pixelpipe/the-anatomy-of-a-module.md) for an example.\n"
msgstr "Utilisez des références si vous avez besoin d'annoter une image (c.-à-d. Marquez des parties de l'image avec une lettre ou un chiffre, puis expliquez la signification dans un texte suivant l'image). Ne placez pas de mots directement dans l'image pour les annotations, car cela rend la localisation difficile. Voir [cette page](../darkroom/pixelpipe/the-anatomy-of-a-module.md) pour un exemple.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changes to the content should be proposed via pull request or a similar mechanism\n"
msgstr "Les modifications du contenu doivent être proposées via une pull request ou un mécanisme similaire\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Your submissions will be copy-edited -- don't take it personally\n"
msgstr "Vos soumissions seront modifiées -- ne le prenez pas mal\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "definition lists"
msgstr "listes de définitions"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The standard method of presenting information about darktable module controls is with the use of definition lists. \n"
msgstr "La méthode standard de présentation des informations concernant les contrôles des modules de darktable consiste à utiliser des listes de définitions. \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gui control name\n"
": A declaration of what the control does. For example \"Set the exposure in EV units\".\n"
msgstr ""
"nom d'un contrôle de l'interface graphique\n"
": Une déclaration de ce que fait le contrôle. Par exemple \"Réglez l'exposition en unités EV\"\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ": You can include as many paragraphs as you like, but try to limit to 2 or 3 where possible.\n"
msgstr ": Vous pouvez inclure autant de paragraphes que vous le souhaitez, mais essayez de limiter leur nombre à 2 ou 3 si possible.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"![active-icon](./contributing/active-icon.png#icon) a control accessed through a button with an icon\n"
": When a control is activated using an icon, take a screenshot of the icon using the standard darktable theme and add it before the name of the control\n"
msgstr ""
"![active-icon](./contributing/active-icon.png#icon) un contrôle accessible via un bouton avec une icône\n"
": Lorsqu'un contrôle est activé à l'aide d'une icône, prenez une capture d'écran de l'icône en utilisant le thème standard de darktable et ajoutez-le avant le nom du contrôle\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gui combobox name\n"
": Comboboxes often have multiple options that all need to be displayed with separate definitions. Use bulleted lists with _italics_ for the combobox values.\n"
": - _the first value_: What the first value means\n"
": - _the second value_: What the second value means\n"
msgstr ""
"nom de la zone de liste déroulante de l'interface\n"
": Les les zones de liste déroulante ont souvent plusieurs options qui doivent toutes être affichées avec des définitions séparées. Utilisez des listes à puces avec _italiques_ pour les valeurs de la zone de liste déroulante.\n"
": - _la première valeur_ : ce que signifie la première valeur\n"
": - _la seconde valeur_ : ce que signifie la seconde valeur\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Definition lists are also used throughout the document, wherever a named piece of functionality needs to be defined. See, for example, [darktable-cli](./program-invocation/darktable-cli.md).\n"
msgstr "Les listes de définitions sont également utilisées dans tout le document, partout où une fonctionnalité nommée doit être définie. Voir, par exemple, [darktable-cli](./program-invocation/darktable-cli.md).\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "notes"
msgstr "remarques"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you wish to present an important note to the user, use the following format:\n"
msgstr "Si vous souhaitez présenter une remarque importante à l'utilisateur, utilisez le format suivant :\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Note**: This is an important note.\n"
msgstr "**Remarque** : Ceci est une remarque importante.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "fixed-width fonts and code blocks"
msgstr "polices à largeur fixe et blocs de code"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fixed width fonts (using the \\` character) should normally only be used for code blocks and when referencing file names and command line parameters.\n"
msgstr "Les polices à largeur fixe (utilisant le caractère \\`) ne doivent normalement être utilisées que pour les blocs de code et lors du référencement des noms de fichiers et des paramètres de la ligne de commande.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "links"
msgstr "liens"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Internal links must be relative to the current file and must point to a valid markdown (.md) file. Start links with either `./` to represent the current directory or `../` to represent the parent directory.\n"
msgstr "Les liens internes doivent être relatifs au fichier actuel et doivent pointer vers un fichier markdown (.md) valide. Commencez les liens avec soit `./` Pour représenter le répertoire courant ou `../` pour représenter le répertoire parent.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Links to a processing module should be in italics, e.g. [_exposure_](../module-reference/processing-modules/exposure.md)\n"
msgstr "Les liens vers un module de traitement doivent être en italique, par ex. [_exposition_](../module-reference/processing-modules/exposure.md)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Links to a utility module should be in plaintext, e.g. [history stack](../module-reference/utility-modules/darkroom/history-stack.md)\n"
msgstr "Les liens vers un module utilitaire doivent être en texte brut, par exemple [historique](../module-reference/utility-modules/darkroom/history-stack.md)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Link to a top level section by referencing the `_index.md` file, e.g. [module reference](../module-reference/_index.md)\n"
msgstr "Lien vers une section de niveau supérieur en référençant le fichier `_index.md`, par ex. [référence des modules](../module-reference/_index.md)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Link to a tab in the preferences dialog: [preferences > general](../preferences-settings/general.md)\n"
msgstr "Lien vers un onglet dans la boîte de dialogue des préférences : [préférences > général](../preferences-settings/general.md)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Link to a specific preference setting: [preferences > general > interface language](../preferences-settings/general.md)\n"
msgstr "Lien vers un paramètre spécifique des préférences : [préférences > général > langue pour l'interface](../preferences-settings/general.md)\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Each header within a page can be linked to directly with an anchor link: [contributing/notes](./contributing.md#notes)\n"
msgstr "Chaque en-tête d'une page peut être lié directement avec un lien d'ancrage : [contribution/remarques](./contributing.md#notes)\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "images"
msgstr "images"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "When taking screenshots from the darktable application itself, use the default darktable theme.\n"
msgstr "Lorsque vous prenez des captures d'écran de l'application darktable elle-même, utilisez le thème darktable par défaut.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Several filename suffixes can be used to control how an image is rendered.\n"
msgstr "Plusieurs suffixes de nom de fichier peuvent être utilisés pour contrôler la façon dont une image est rendue.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"icon\n"
": To insert an image as an icon, include `#icon` after the image name in the link. The markdown `![squirrel icon](./contributing/contributing.png#icon)` outputs the following: ![squirrel icon](./contributing/squirrel.png#icon)\n"
msgstr ""
"icône\n"
": Pour insérer une image sous forme d'icône, incluez `#icon` après le nom de l'image dans le lien. Le markdown `![squirrel icon](./contributing/contributing.png#icon)` affiche ce qui suit : ![squirrel icon](./contributing/squirrel.png#icon)\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"image width\n"
": You can set the image width to 25, 33, 50, 66, 75 or 100 per cent of the rendered page width by including `#wxx` after the image name in the link, where `xx` is the desired width. For example:\n"
": `![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w25)` outputs\n"
": ![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w25)\n"
": `![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w75)` outputs\n"
": ![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w75)\n"
msgstr ""
"largeur de l'image\n"
": Vous pouvez définir la largeur de l'image à 25, 33, 50, 66, 75 ou 100% de la largeur de la page rendue en incluant `#wxx` après le nom de l'image dans le lien, où `xx` est la largeur souhaitée. Par exemple :\n"
": `![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w25)` affiche\n"
": ![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w25)\n"
": `![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w75)` affiche\n"
": ![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w75)\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"inline\n"
": With the exception of icons, images are included as block elements by default. You can override this by including `#inline` after the image name. This can be combined with the width setting as follows.\n"
": `![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w25#inline)` outputs ![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w25#inline) \n"
msgstr ""
"en ligne\n"
": À l'exception des icônes, les images sont incluses en tant qu'éléments de bloc par défaut. Vous pouvez remplacer cela en incluant `#inline` après le nom de l'image. Cela peut être combiné avec le paramètre de largeur comme suit.\n"
": `![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w25#inline)` affiche ![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w25#inline) \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"default\n"
": By default images are presented as block elements with 100% width. So `![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png#w100)` and `![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png)` are equivalent and both output the following:\n"
": ![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png)\n"
msgstr ""
"défaut\n"
": Par défaut, les images sont présentées sous forme d'éléments de bloc avec une largeur de 100%. Donc `![squirrel](./contribution/squirrel.png#w100)` et `![squirrel](./contribution/squirrel.png)` sont équivalents et les deux produisent ce qui suit :\n"
": ![squirrel](./contributing/squirrel.png)\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "midi device support"
msgstr "prise en charge des périphériques midi"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The shortcut mapping system has been most extensively tested with the Behringer X-Touch Mini and contains custom code to deal with the specific features of this device. All other devices are treated as \"generic midi\" and may or may not work (well) or need some manual setup each time. A configuration framework (possibly in lua) to support additional device-specific features is on the to do list.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Behringer X-touch Mini"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The device should be in Standard Mode (not MC). Layers A & B are somewhat supported, however, since the device does not send a notification when switching between layers, and since the updates to \"hidden\" rotors and lights (both under buttons and the pattern used around the rotors) are ignored, everything will only be updated completely after you press or turn something in the \"new\" layer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The light rings around the rotors show a different pattern depending on whether the associated slider has a symmetrical +/- range centered around 0, 0-100 (or 0-1) or anything else. If linked to a drop-down (or star rating) the rotor will step one light at the time. If the drop-down has many (more than 13) items (like the blending mode drop-down), the rotor will go around twice; the first time with one light on, and the second time with two adjacent lights.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Arturia Beatstep"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Individual rotors can be configured to send absolute (0-127) values or changes (+/- 1,2,3,... in different encodings). The recommended setting is Relative #1 for all knobs with Knob Acceleration set to Slow (Off) or Medium. This can be configured with [Midi Control Center](https://www.arturia.com/support/downloads&manuals), available for Windows or MacOS. By default the darktable midi module assumes, for unknown devices, that rotors use absolute encodings. After startup it therefore needs to be told that the device is sending relative movements. You can do this by turning one of the encoders slowly left (down) 5 times. This allows the module to determine which of the several relative encodings is used. If you don't succeed switching encodings on the first attempt, you can reinitialise the input modules by pressing Ctrl+Shift+Alt+I and try again. If you still have problems, you could try [this](https://wd40.co.uk/product/fast-drying-contact-cleaner/).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you map the Beatstep's buttons to ratings, color labels or toggle buttons, they should light up when the corresponding element is switched on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Behringer BCR2000 "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "(and possibly BCF2000)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "These machines are highly configurable so there are many settings that could complicate the interaction with darktable's midi module. The [BC Manager tool](https://mountainutilities.eu/bcmanager) (available for Windows and MacOS) can be used to configure them. The easiest thing to do is to reset all encoders and buttons to their simplest settings, which can be done (for the BCR2000) using [this file](https://github.com/dterrahe/darktable/files/6539400/bcr2000.all.buttons.and.encoders.zip). You can send it to the machine with BC Manager or (under Linux) with amidi. There's also a global setting called \"Deadtime\" that determines how long the BCR ignores arriving messages after sending out updates. This is to avoid feedback loops, but for darktable it means that it blocks the adjustments sent back immediately after each rotor move. So Deadtime needs to be set to 0.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once configured in this way, button and rotor lights should all work. The top row of rotors (or the only row for the BCF2000) support different light patterns (like the X-Touch Midi, with some extra options and it has 15 instead of 13 leds). However, configuring these is more complicated, and not yet implemented. It also seems to be slower, so may not be doable in real-time for each update (like it is done for the X-touch). So at the moment only the 12-dot pattern is used. For rotors linked to drop-down lists, just like on the X-touch the rotor, the light goes round twice; for the first 15 options only one light goes on, for the second 15 options, two adjacent lights will be on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loupedeck "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "(and Loupedeck+ but not the later non-midi devices) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Going by the information provided [here](https://discuss.pixls.us/t/midi-controller-for-darktable/2582/92), most of the functionality of the first two loupedeck models (both midi based) should be supported, with the following exceptions and caveats:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "the Hue/Sat/Lum buttons can be mapped to the notebook tabs in the color zones module but the little lights next to them may not respond to update messages sent when the user switches tabs using the mouse, so they might get out of sync\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "the 8 sliders/wheels can be individually mapped to the elements of the graph in color zones\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Other than that, since the loupedeck uses Relative encoding (so is similar to the Beatstep) it will need to tell the midi module at each startup (until a configuration system has been implemented). You do this by turning any of the knobs (or wheels) slowly down/left 5 times. Re-initialise the input layer with Ctrl+Shift+Alt+I if it didn't work the first time so you can try again.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Korg nanoKONTROL2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "The device should be configured first using the Korg Kontrol Editor application to be in the CC mode and every button should be set to the Note type and Momentary button behavior. To control the lights in the buttons the LED mode should be set to External. It is important to note that the Track and the Marker buttons do not have leds in them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/special-topics/midi-device-support.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is an Kontrol Editor profile available [here](https://github.com/darktable-org/darktable/files/7603658/note_buttons.zip) which can be loaded using the Windows application to directly configure all these settings to correctly work with darktable.\n"
msgstr ""

